title.narrative: Output 3.2: Children and their caregivers have access to improved and sustainable water, sanitation, and hygiene services in primary schools and health facilities

description.narrative: By October 2019, UNICEF had supported 149 primary schools to meet the WASH child-friendly school criteria, and the same number of schools gained access to basic WASH services during the reporting year through UNICEF direct support. The WASH services in the 149 schools are serving an additional 38,726 students (20,264 boys and 18,462 girls). Funding for WASH in one health-care facility was not secured and the output was discontinued at the mid-year review. | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/12/2019
